<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4441998>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Macedomeris ivoi gen. et sp. nov. (IZB) A. Paratype subadult male, habitus, lateral view. B. Paratype female I, head, anterior view. C. Paratype female I, head and thoracic shield, anterolateral view. D. Paratype male, collum, dorsal view. E. Holotype male, collum, dorsal view. F. Paratype female I, thoracic shield, left lateral view. G. Paratype female II, right side of the head, anterior view. H. Paratype female II, left thoracic pit, lateral view. I. Holotype male, anal shield, posterior view. Abbreviations: as: anal shield; c: collum; to: organ of Tömösváry; ts: thoracic shield; r1, r2, r3: ridges on collum and thoracic shield; r2a, r2b: parts of thoracic r2; the numbers indicate tergites. White arrows indicate sclerotized nodules in C or vestigial ommatidia in G. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A–F, H, I), 0.1 mm (G)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4441998/files/figure.png" .

